		<IUseCase type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID 520a8701-539c-4b3c-bae1-0b809c0357f9</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Relay_Storm_Info</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">1.2.1990::0:0:0</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_description type="p"><IDescription type="e">
				<_textRTF type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\b\fs20 Pre-Condition\par%0D
\b0 1) -\par%0D
\par%0D
\b Trigger\par%0D
\b0 1) The Predict_strom_scenario predicts a storm with over 60%25 probability\b\par%0D
\par%0D
Post-Condition\par%0D
\b0 1) The Governments of the affected areas are informed about the strom\par%0D
2) The Emergency Responders and News Outlets of the affected areas are informed about the storm if the probability is over 90%25\par%0D
\b\par%0D
Main Scenario\par%0D
\b0 1) The system determines that a storm occurs with over 60%25 probability in a certain region\par%0D
2) It is determined which News Outlets, Government and Emergency Responders correspond to the affected areas\par%0D
3) A message is generated containing the forecast, risks and referal to the provided Weather info to remain up-to-date, in the relevant language.\par%0D
4) The message is send by Email to the relevant Governments\b\par%0D
\par%0D
Alternative Scenario\par%0D
\b0 1) If an actor is already informed about the storm, no new Email is send\par%0D
2) If the actor is not available by email, an SMS will be send\par%0D
3) If there are no News Outlets, Government or Emergency Responders which correspond to the affected areas, noone will be informed, and no message is generated\par%0D
4) If the probability is over 90%25, the relevant Emergency responders and News Outlets are also informed\par%0D
\b\par%0D
}%0D
</_textRTF>
			</IDescription>
			</_description>
