		<IUseCase type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID ca3129d4-5d70-4d14-a8eb-29059255cf67</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Predict_storm_scenario</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">1.2.1990::0:0:0</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_description type="p"><IDescription type="e">
				<_textRTF type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\b\fs20 Pre-Condition\par%0D
\b0 1) New sensor data since the last prediction is available in the data storage\par%0D
\par%0D
\b Trigger\par%0D
\b0 1) The predictions are made periodically with a period of 1 minute\b\par%0D
\par%0D
Post-Condition\b0\par%0D
1) If a storm is predicted, the associated data is send to Relay_Storm_Info and Relay_Evacuation_Info\par%0D
\b\par%0D
Main Scenario\par%0D
\b0 1) New sensor data is read from the data storage\par%0D
2) Using a machine learning algrorithm, the location, probability and severity of storms are calculated\par%0D
3) If a storm is predicted with over 60%25 probability the relevant data is send to Relay_Storm_Info and Relay_Evacuation\b\par%0D
\par%0D
Alternative Scenario\par%0D
\b0 1) If no storm is predicted with over 60%25 probability, the system does not output anything\par%0D
\par%0D
\par%0D
\par%0D
\par%0D
\par%0D
}%0D
</_textRTF>
			</IDescription>
			</_description>
